==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
From ''echino'' "spiny" + ''derm'' "skin"
===Noun===
'''echinoderm'''
#Any member of the [[Echinodermata]], a group of [[radial]]ly [[symmetric]], spiny-skinned [[marine]] [[animal]]s. Examples of echinoderms include [[seastar]]s, [[sea urchin]]s, [[sea cucumber]]s, [[crinoid]]s, and [[sand dollar]]s.

